description: 105, an isolation window of 0.4 m/z, a maximum injection time of 100 msec and a normalized collision energy of 32. Dynamic exclusion was set to 30 sec. Raw data were directly analyzed against the Swiss-Prot database restricted to Mus musculus using Proteome Discoverer version 2.2 with Mascot search engine version 2.5 for identification and TMT quantification. Peptides and proteins were filtered at a false-discovery rate (FDR) of 1 % using the percolator node and the protein FDR validator node, respectively.
